@node Main "gcj.guide"
@next "Copying"

Introduction
************

This manual describes how to use @{b}gcj@{ub}, the GNU compiler for the Java
programming language.  @{b}gcj@{ub} can generate both @{b}.class@{ub} files and object
files, and it can read both Java source code and @{b}.class@{ub} files.


 @{" Copying         " link "Copying"}  The GNU General Public License
 @{" GNU Free Documentation License " link "GNU Free Documentation License"}  
			How you can share and copy this manual
 @{" Invoking gcj    " link "Invoking gcj"}  Compiler options supported by @{b}gcj@{ub}
 @{" Compatibility   " link "Compatibility"}  Compatibility between gcj and other tools for Java
 @{" Invoking gcjh   " link "Invoking gcjh"}  Generate header files from class files
 @{" Invoking jv-scan " link "Invoking jv-scan"}  Print information about source files
 @{" Invoking jcf-dump " link "Invoking jcf-dump"}  Print information about class files
 @{" Invoking gij    " link "Invoking gij"}  Interpreting Java bytecodes
 @{" Invoking jv-convert " link "Invoking jv-convert"}  Converting from one encoding to another
 @{" Invoking rmic   " link "Invoking rmic"}  Generate stubs for Remote Method Invocation.
 @{" Invoking rmiregistry " link "Invoking rmiregistry"}  The remote object registry.
 @{" About CNI       " link "About CNI"}  Description of the Compiled Native Interface
 @{" System properties " link "System properties"}  Modifying runtime behavior of the libgcj library
 @{" Resources       " link "Resources"}  Where to look for more information

@endnode

